# Chapter 2
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter2.title=Introduction
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter2.page1.text=Welcome to the Armourer's Workshop Guide Book.&pThis book will help you get started with Armourer's Workshop.&pIt is recommended that you work through the book in order.
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter2.page2.text=Armourer's Workshop will let you build you're own armour with a custom look!

# Chapter 3
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter3.title=Multi-Block
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter3.page1.text=The first thing you will need to get started building you're custom armour is the armourer multiblock.&pThe Armourer multiblock is build using 79 Armourer Wall's, 4 Armourer Corner's and 1 Armourer Brain.
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter3.page2.text=The multiblock is a 22*22 structure with Armourer Wall's along the edges and a Armourer Corner in each corner.&pThe Armourer Brain can be placed in any edge but CAN NOT be placed at a corner.
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter3.page3.text=The Armourer also need a large 20*20*20 space above it to operate.&p&n&image1
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter3.page4.text=&image2&p&p&p&image3

# Chapter 4
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter4.title=Armour Templates
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter4.page1.text=Armour Templates come in 5 variants Head, Chest, Legs, Skirt and Feet.&pTo select what type of custom armour you would like to build, craft the Armour Template of the same type and insert it into the Armourer Brain.

# Chapter 5
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter5.title=Armour Cubes
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter5.page1.text=Armour Cubes are the main building block for custom armour. Simply place them around the player projection, then colour them to you're liking.&pArmour Cubes also have a glowing variant, that will glow in the dark!

# Chapter 6
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter6.title=Painting Tools
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter6.page1.text=A number of painting tool have been provided to help with you're creative endeavour!&pColour Mixer&nAllows you to mix up any colour you like.&pPaintbrush&nPaints a single Armour Cube.
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter6.page2.text=Colour Picker&nLets you pick a colour from an Armour Cube and set a Colour Mixer to that colour.&pPaint Roller&nPaints Armour Cube's in a 3*3*1 area.
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter6.page3.text=Burn Tool&nMakes an Armour Cube darker.&pDodge Tool&nMakes an Armour Cube lighter.&pColour Noise Tool&nApplies random colour noise to an Armour Cube.
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter6.page4.text=Shade Noise Tool&nApplies random shading to am Armour Cube.

# Chapter 7
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter7.title=Armour Crafter
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter7.page1.text=The last part of creating you're custom armour is the Armour Crafter. To use the Armour Crafter save an armour design onto an Armour Template using the Armourer Brain.&pNext up place the Armour Template and some normal
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter7.page2.text=armour of the same type inside the Armour Crafter.&pExample a Head Armour Template and a Diamond Helmet would create a Custom Diamond Head Armour with the same protection statistics as diamond.
book.armourersworkshop:guideBook.chapter7.page3.text=Now press create and you have you're every own custom armour.&pNote: Skirt amour requires leg armour as the normal armour type in the Armour Crafter